type="external">erct-000L.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>For any <fr:link
href="erct-000B.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000B">precategory</fr:link> <fr:tex>C</fr:tex>, the type <fr:tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( D :  \mathsf {Precategory} \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( D :  \mathsf {Precategory} \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( D :  \mathsf {Precategory} \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( D :  \mathsf {Precategory} \right ) \mathclose {} } } {D \cong  C}</fr:tex> of <fr:link
href="erct-000J.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000J">isomorphisms of precategories</fr:link> onto <fr:tex>C</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="erct-001H.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001H">contractible</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2937</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:addr>#364</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-364.xml</fr:route><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>3</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>erct-000L</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>The type of isomorphisms onto <fr:tex>C</fr:tex> is inhabited, considering the identity isomorphism <fr:tex>1_{ C } \colon  C \cong  C</fr:tex>. Therefore, it suffices to show that the type of <fr:link
href="erct-000J.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000J">isomorphisms</fr:link> onto <fr:tex>C</fr:tex> depicted below is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link>:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block">     \begin {aligned}     D &amp;:  \mathsf {Precategory} \\      F &amp;: D \cong  C     \end {aligned}   </fr:tex>

  <fr:p>We unfold the definitions of a <fr:link
href="erct-000B.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000B">precategories</fr:link> and <fr:link
href="erct-000J.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000J">their isomorphisms</fr:link>, dropping <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">propositional</fr:link> axioms:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block">      \begin {aligned}       D_0&amp;:  \mathsf {Type} \\        D_1&amp;:D_0 \to  D_0 \to \mathsf {Set} \\        F_0&amp;: D_0 \to  C_0 \\        F_1&amp;:  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }  D_1xy \to   C \mathopen {} \left ( F_0x , F_0y \right ) \mathclose {} \\        h_1 &amp;:  \mathsf {isBiinvertible} \, F_0 \\        h_2 &amp;:  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }   \mathsf {isPropMap} \mathopen {} \left ( F_1xy \right ) \mathclose {}         \\        h_3 &amp;:  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }   \mathsf {isSurjection} \mathopen {} \left ( F_1xy \right ) \mathclose {}       \end {aligned}   </fr:tex>

  <fr:p>A function that is both <fr:link
href="erct-001T.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001T">propositional</fr:link> and a <fr:link
href="erct-0029.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0029">surjection</fr:link>, i.e. a <fr:link
href="erct-003F.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-003F">bijection</fr:link>, is an <fr:link
href="erct-000V.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000V">equivalence</fr:link> by <fr:ref
addr="erct-002Z"
href="erct-002Z.xml"
taxon="Corollary"></fr:ref>. We can therefore repackage our telescope equivalently:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block">      \begin {aligned}       D_0&amp;:  \mathsf {Type} \\        D_1&amp;:D_0 \to  D_0 \to \mathsf {Set} \\        F_0&amp;: D_0 \cong  C_0 \\        F_1&amp;:  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }  D_1xy \cong   C \mathopen {} \left ( F_0x , F_0y \right ) \mathclose {}       \end {aligned}   </fr:tex>

  <fr:p>By the univalence principle for types, we may contract <fr:tex>\mathopen {} \left ( D_0,F_0 \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex> to <fr:tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \left \lvert C \right \rvert ,  1_{ \left \lvert C \right \rvert } \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex>:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block">      \begin {aligned}       D_1&amp;: \left \lvert C \right \rvert \to   \left \lvert C \right \rvert \to \mathsf {Set} \\        F_1&amp;:  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  C \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  C \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  C \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  C \right ) \mathclose {} } }  D_1xy \cong   C \mathopen {} \left ( x , y \right ) \mathclose {}       \end {aligned}   </fr:tex>

  <fr:p>Next we rewrite using the univalence principles for functions and families of types (<fr:ref
addr="erct-0015"
href="erct-0015.xml"
taxon="Axiom"></fr:ref>, <fr:ref
addr="erct-001D"
href="erct-001D.xml"
taxon="Axiom"></fr:ref>):</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block">      \begin {aligned}       D_1&amp;: \left \lvert C \right \rvert \to   \left \lvert C \right \rvert \to \mathsf {Set} \\        F_1&amp;: D_1 =  \lambda x,y \mathpunct {.} { C \mathopen {} \left ( x , y \right ) \mathclose {} }      \end {aligned}   </fr:tex>

  <fr:p>By the <fr:link
href="erct-0015.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0015">univalence principle for functions</fr:link>, the data above is <fr:link
href="erct-001H.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001H">contractible</fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
